-- Rio shares surge after ends Chinalco, JVs with BHP
-- 
-- Thu Jun 4, 2009 9:26pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/06/05/us-riotinto-chinalco-shares-sb-idUSTRE5540DK20090605

 

 SYDNEY  (Reuters) - Shares in global miner Rio Tinto surged over 12 percent on Friday after it said it had scrapped its proposed $19.5 billion tie-up with Chinese firm Chinalco on Friday and instead launched a heavily discounted $15.2 billion right issue. 

 Rio Tinto traded at A$73.70, up 10.2 percent, at 0125 GMT. (Reporting by  Jonathan Standing )